<TITLE> Hasina needs better care: aunt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 22 (bdnews24.com)  Detained former prime minister Sheikh Hasina needs medical treatment, according to her aunt Sheikh Khadiza Begum Lily. "Sheikh Hasina is not well. She has problem with her eyes. She needs medical treatment," Khadiza told bdnews24.com Saturday after seeing Hasina the previous day. The Awami League chief's husband Wazed Miah and Khadiza visited her in the special jail housed in the Jatiya Sangsad Bhaban complex on Eid day Friday. Hasina's aunt said her niece required better care. Khadiza added that relatives should be permitted to visit Hasina regularly and asked the people to pray for Hasina. Khadiza is the youngest sister of assassinated independence leader Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. bdnews24
